# Sunway ERP frontend

React · TypeScript · Vite · Tailwind · shadcn/ui · sonner

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev
npm run build
```

## Structure

| Path | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `src/pages/` | Route-level screens by product area |
| `src/modules/` | Large HR sub-features (forms, shells) |
| `src/service/` | API clients (`apiClient`, `*Service.ts`) |
| `src/types/` | Shared TypeScript types |
| `src/lib/` | Columns, helpers (`api-error-message.ts`) |
| `src/components/` | Shared UI + `ui/` (shadcn) |
| `src/schema/` | Zod schemas where used |

Alias `@/` → `src/`.

## Product areas (pages)

| Area | Typical path |
|------|----------------|
| Dashboard | `pages/dashboard.tsx` |
| HR / employees | `pages/employees-page.tsx`, `employee-profile-page.tsx`, `modules/hr/` |
| Admin / company | `pages/admin/hr/`, `pages/hr/` |
| Inventory | `pages/inventory/` |
| Purchase | `pages/purchase/` |
| Sales | `pages/sales/` |
| Finance | `pages/finance/` |
| Settings / profile | `pages/settings/`, `pages/profile/`, `user-profile-page.tsx` |
| Auth | `pages/auth/` |

When adding UI, copy patterns from the **same product folder** (list + detail + dialog, `PageHeader`, toast errors).

## API

- `apiClient` → backend `/api/...`
- Map DTOs in `*Service.ts` (see `purchaseFlowService.ts`, `salesFlowService.ts`, `hr.service.ts`)
- Errors: `getApiErrorMessage(error, fallback)` from `@/lib/api-error-message`
- Show **toast** and, for forms, an **inline alert** when save/submit can fail on server rules

## UI habits

- `CurrencyAmount` for money (including edit forms and line totals)
- Confirm dialogs before irreversible or financial actions when the module already does
- Functional components + hooks
- Keep `.tsx` components **under 250 lines** — see **`split-large-components.mdc`**

## Git

Commit only when the user asks. No Co-authored-by or agent branding.

## Agent-maintained docs

If you introduce a reusable pattern not already in rules/skills, append it per **`capture-knowledge.mdc`** (same session, before you finish).
